    <body>
        <p>You can make the grid "sticky," so that when you drag<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare,Products.Contributor"> frames</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> objects</MadCap:conditionalText><span MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">images</span> around the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare,Products.Contributor"> page</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> frame</MadCap:conditionalText><span MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">editor</span>, the edge is automatically attached to the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare,Products.Contributor"> page</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> frame</MadCap:conditionalText><span MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</span> in relation to the nearest vertical or horizontal line of dots. Otherwise, if you do not have this option set, the position of the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare,Products.Contributor"> frames</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> objects</MadCap:conditionalText><span MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">images</span> will be "loose" on the page.</p>
